pullRequest.body:
This adds definitions of the `k`-smooth numbers up to and including `N` as a `Finset` and of its complement in `{1, ..., N}` plus some API, in particular cardinality bounds. There are also a few additional API lemmas for `Nat.primesBelow` and `Nat.smoothNumbers` (including a decidability instance for membership in the latter).

This is a PR in preparation of the divergence of the sum of the reciprocals of the primes. See [here](https://leanprover.zulipchat.com/#narrow/stream/217875-Is-there-code-for-X.3F/topic/Sum.20over.201.2Fp.20diverges/near/409835682) on Zulip.

```
Error: ./././Mathlib/Algebra/BigOperators/Basic.lean:602:59: error: unexpected token '@['; expected 'abbrev', 'alias', 'axiom', 'binder_predicate', 'builtin_initialize', 'class', 'def', 'elab', 'elab_rules', 'example', 'inductive', 'infix', 'infixl', 'infixr', 'initialize', 'instance', 'irreducible_def', 'lemma', 'macro', 'macro_rules', 'notation', 'notation3', 'opaque', 'postfix', 'prefix', 'proof_wanted', 'scoped', 'structure', 'syntax' or 'theorem'
```
In my copy of Mathlib, this line is
```lean
  refine' Eq.trans _ (prod_sigma s t fun p => f (p.1, p.2))
```
so I have no idea what this error is about...

Probably that's due to the other PR #9237 in the same batch. Indeed the [failed build there](https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/pull/9237#issuecomment-1870587280) shows the same error.
